text: Jacques Diouf (1 August 1938 – 17 August 2019) was a Senegalese diplomat. He was the Director-General of the United Nations' Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) from January 1994 to 31 December 2011. Diouf was born in Saint-Louis, Senegal. Diouf died on 17 August 2019 in Paris after a long- illness, 16 days after his 81st birthday.Le diplomate sénégalais Jacques Diouf est décédé à l'âge de 81 ans ==References== Category:1938 births Category:2019 deaths Category:African diplomats Category:Senegalese people
